'''Mohammad Hossein Kanaanizadegan''' ({{langx|fa|محمد حسین کنعانی زادگان}}; born 23 March 1994), known as '''Hossein Kanaani''', is an Iranian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] club [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] and [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 June 2016|title=Esteghlal signs Persepolis defender Kanaanizadegan|url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/403407/Esteghlal-signs-Persepolis-defender-Kanaanizadegan|access-date=15 February 2021|website=Tehran Times|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Hossein Kanani Stats, Info and Next Game|url=https://www.footballcritic.com/hossein-kanani/profile/34240|access-date=28 April 2021|website=FootballCritic|language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Persepolis===
He joined [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in January 2012. He signed a {{frac|2|1|2}}-year contract until the end of 2013–14 season with the club.<ref>[http://www.perspolisnews.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=26506:%DA%A9%D9%86%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF-2-5-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%B6%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D8%AF&catid=45:transfer&Itemid=68 perspolisnews.com]</ref> He made his debut for Persepolis as a starter against [[Foolad F.C.|Foolad]] in the final fixture of the [[2011–12 Iran Pro League]].<ref>[http://www.iplstats.com/website11-12/Week34/FOL_PER_34.htm iplstas.com]</ref> He played for [[Persepolis F.C. Academy|Persepolis U21]] in AFC Vision Asia U21 Tehran Premier League.

===Loan to Beira Mar===
Kanaani joined Portuguese club [[Beira Mar]] on loan in August 2013, but due to work permit issues he returned to Iran without playing a match.

===Loan to Malavan===
He joined [[Malavan F.C.|Malavan]] on a two–year loan to spend his conscription period in summer 2014. Kanaani scored his first goal for Malavan in a 1–1 draw against [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]].

===Esteghlal===
In May 2016, after completing his two–year conscription period at Malavan, it was thought Kanaani would return to his original club, Persepolis. However, Kanaani rejected Persepolis' offer and joined rivals Esteghlal. Shortly after joining the club, Kanaani suffered a season-ending injury after only playing two games. He was released by Esteghlal at the end of the season having only played two games for the club.

=== Saipa ===
He played the [[2017–18 Persian Gulf Pro League|2017–18 season]] for [[Saipa F.C.|Saipa FC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://iscanews.ir:80/news.aspx?id=803562&title=کنعانی-زادگان-به-سایپا-پیوست|title=کنعانی زادگان به سایپا پیوست|date=4 July 2017|website=iscanews.ir|language=fa|access-date=7 July 2019}}</ref>

=== Machine Sazi ===
He joined [[Machine Sazi F.C.|Machine Sazi]] for the [[2018–19 Persian Gulf Pro League|2018–19 season]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.parsnews.com/بخش-%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B2%D8%B4%DB%8C-7/526774-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C%DA%A9%D9%86-%D8%AC%D9%86%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%84%DB%8C-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B4%DB%8C%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B4%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C-%D9%BE%DB%8C%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%AA|title=کنعانی زادگان به ماشین سازی پیوست|website=پارس نیوز|language=fa|access-date=7 July 2019}}</ref> He finished the 2018–19 Persian Gulf Pro League at Machine Sazi F.C. with 27 appearances and 1 goal.

=== Persepolis ===
[[File:Hossein Kanaanizadegan Goal Celebration Persepolis FC.jpg|thumb|Kanaanizadegan celebrating his goal against [[Sanat Naft Abadan F.C.|Naft Abadan]] in September 2019]]
On 7 July 2019, Kanaanizadegan signed a two-year<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.isna.ir/news/98041608417/کنعانی-زادگان-با-پرسپولیس-دو-ساله-بست|title=کنعانی‌زادگان با پرسپولیس دو ساله بست|date=7 July 2019|website=ایسنا|language=fa|access-date=7 July 2019}}</ref> contract with [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] champions Persepolis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://video.varzesh3.com/video/195175/کنعانی-زادگان-آمده-ام-همه-چیز-را-جبران-کنم|title=ویدیو ورزش سه {{!}} کنعانی زادگان : آمده ام همه چیز را جبران کنم|website=ویدیو ورزش سه|date=7 July 2019 |language=fa|access-date=7 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.khabarvarzeshi.com/fa/news/218780|title=کنعانی‌زادگان: عاشق پرسپولیسم؛ ‌می‌خواهم جبران کنم|last=خبرورزشی|date=7 July 2019|website=fa|language=fa|access-date=7 July 2019}}</ref> Kanaanizadegan scored his first goal for Persepolis in a 1–0 victory over [[Sanat Naft Abadan F.C.|Sanat Naft Abadan]] on 16 September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1398/06/25/2097807|title=لیگ برتر فوتبال{{!}} پرسپولیس با شکست صنعت نفت به استقبال دربی 90 رفت/ امتیاز 6 با شماره 6- اخبار ورزشی - اخبار تسنیم - Tasnim|website=خبرگزاری تسنیم - Tasnim|language=fa|access-date=16 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1637034/%D8%A7%D8%B4%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%87-%D8%AF%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D9%88-%DA%AF%D9%84-%D8%B4%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%87-%D8%B4%D8%B4-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%B3|title=گل شماره شش پرسپولیس|website=www.varzesh3.com|access-date=16 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=AFC Champions League {{!}} AFC|url=https://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-champions-league/teams/605/1969/424889|access-date=22 April 2021|website=the-AFC|language=en-GB}}</ref>

=== Al Ahli ===
On 2 August 2021, Kanaanizadegan joined [[Qatar]]i top flight football club [[Al Ahli SC (Doha)|Al Ahli]] on a two-year deal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-08-02 |title=Persepolis defender Kanaanizadegan joins Qatar's Al Ahli |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/463618/Persepolis-defender-Kanaanizadegan-joins-Qatar-s-Al-Ahli |access-date=2023-07-20 |website=Tehran Times |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Iran's Kanaanizadegan Signs for Al-Ahli - Sports news |url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2021/08/02/2547728/iran-s-kanaanizadegan-signs-for-al-ahli |access-date=2023-07-20 |website=Tasnim News Agency |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-08-04 |title=کنعانی‌زادگان رسما به الاهلی پیوست |url=https://www.isna.ir/news/1400051309664/کنعانی-زادگان-رسما-به-الاهلی-پیوست |access-date=2023-07-20 |website=ایسنا |language=fa}}</ref> His performance in the new team led to new offers from Iran.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-08-23 |title=کنعانی‌ زادگان فرشته‌ نجات این‌ روزهای الاهلی+فیلم |url=https://www.imna.ir/news/599147/کنعانی-زادگان-فرشته-نجات-این-روزهای-الاهلی-فیلم |access-date=2023-07-20 |website=ایمنا |language=fa}}</ref>

=== Return to Persepolis ===
On 8 July 2023, Kanaanizadegan signed a new two-year contract with Persepolis.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kanaanizadegan Joins Persepolis: IPL - Sports news |url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2023/07/09/2922831/kanaanizadegan-joins-persepolis-ipl |access-date=2023-07-20 |website=Tasnim News Agency |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-07-08 |title=محمدحسین کنعانی زادگان به پرسپولیس پیوست |url=https://www.mehrnews.com/news/5831157/محمدحسین-کنعانی-زادگان-به-پرسپولیس-پیوست |access-date=2023-07-20 |website=خبرگزاری مهر {{!}} اخبار ایران و جهان {{!}} Mehr News Agency |language=fa}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Iran Iraq Football teams 2.jpg|thumb|Kanaanizadegan playing for [[Iran national football team|Iran]] at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].]]

===U17===

He played two matches at the 2010 Asian U16 Championships.

===U20===
He started in all four games for the 2012 Asian U19 Championship Qualifiers helping the team keep a clean sheet in all of them. He started in Iran's first game during the championships, helping Team Meli keep a clean sheet as well as hitting the bar from 30 meters out. He was part of [[Iran national under-20 football team|Iran U–20]] during the [[2012 AFC U-19 Championship qualification]], [[2012 CIS Cup]], [[2012 AFF U-19 Youth Championship]] and [[2012 AFC U-19 Championship]].

===U23===
He was invited to the [[Iran national under-23 football team|Iran U-23]] training camp by [[Nelo Vingada]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://isport.ir/fa/content/47518/%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3%D8%AA-%DB%B3%DB%B1-%D9%86%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%87-%D9%88%DB%8C%D9%86%DA%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%85-%D9%85%D9%84%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%AF | title=لیست ۳۱ نفره وینگادا برای تیم ملی امید | access-date=7 August 2014 | archive-date=10 December 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181210111147/http://isport.ir/fa/content/47518/%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3%D8%AA-%DB%B3%DB%B1-%D9%86%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%87-%D9%88%DB%8C%D9%86%DA%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%85-%D9%85%D9%84%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%AF | url-status=dead }}</ref> in preparation for [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games|Incheon 2014]] and the 2016 AFC U-22 Championship (Summer Olympic qualification). He was named in the Iran U23 final list for Incheon 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ffiri.ir/news/detail/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C%DA%A9%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%85-%D9%85%D9%84%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%86%DA%86%D8%A6%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%AE%D8%B5-%D8%B4%D8%AF/117027/news.aspx|title=بازیکنان اعزامی تیم ملی امید به اینچئون مشخص شد|publisher=ffiri.ir|access-date=12 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819231500/http://ffiri.ir/news/detail/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C%DA%A9%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%85-%D9%85%D9%84%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%86%DA%86%D8%A6%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%AE%D8%B5-%D8%B4%D8%AF/117027/news.aspx|archive-date=19 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Senior===
Kanaanizadegan made his debut against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] in a friendly match on 11 June 2015. He also played against Turkmenistan on 16 June 2015. He scored his first goal for the team with the third goal in the 14–0 thrashing of [[Cambodia national football team|Cambodia]] in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2022 World Cup Qualifiers]] on 10 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-10-10 |title=فیلم/ گل سوم ایران به کامبوج توسط کنعانی |url=https://www.mashreghnews.ir/news/1000204/فیلم-گل-سوم-ایران-به-کامبوج-توسط-کنعانی |access-date=2023-07-20 |website=مشرق نیوز |language=fa}}</ref> He scored his second goal for the team with a header against [[Syria national football team|Syria]] on 30 March 2021.<ref>{{Citation |title=گل اول ایران به سوریه توسط کنعانی زادگان- ویدیو ورزش سه |date=2021-03-30 |url=https://video.varzesh3.com/video/230522/%DA%AF%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%B1%DB%8C%D9%87-%D8%AA%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%B7-%DA%A9%D9%86%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%86 |access-date=2023-07-20 |publisher=ویدیو ورزش سه |language=fa}}</ref> Scored two goals in a friendly against Qatar on the 17th of October, 2023

